This module provides the result monad.

A result can be either a success or a failure.

In NimScript, it can be used to handle errors without having to raise/catch exceptions. Besides, the NimScript backend does not currently allow to catch exceptions.

Types

Result[S; F] = object
  case successful: bool
  of true:
      success: S

  of false:
      failure: F
